    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-model-adequate",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model adequately predicts absolute hemolysis index for VAD operating envelope",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage accumulation formulation with Lagrangian particle tracking, has been demonstrated across multiple published inter-laboratory studies (Stewart et al. 2012, Hariharan et al. 2011, FDA Critical Path initiative round-robin) to reproduce experimentally measured normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within ±35% across the FDA pump operating envelope. Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis over rheological parameters (viscosity, yield stress) and boundary condition uncertainty (inlet velocity profile ±8%) confirms that prediction intervals remain below the clinical hemolysis threshold of 0.01 g/100 L at all five target flow-speed combinations. The model has therefore been assessed as adequate for absolute hemolysis prediction under VAD conditions at MRL 5, subject to the credibility factor levels documented in this package.",
      "purpose": "Establish model adequacy for regulatory submission supporting Class III VAD clearance",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; 5 operating points: 3–6 L/min at 2000–3500 RPM; blood analogue fluid at 37°C"
    }
  ],
